LOKOJA – The Kogi state Community and Social Development Agency has flagged off the construction of boreholes, clinic and renovation of classrooms at Angwa – Ogebe and Abache Communities in Ankpa Local Government Area of the state. The General Manager of the Agency, Chief Dauda Momoh, while Presenting the Cheques to the Communities, charged them to ensure that a quality job is done within two months. He said  Governor, Yahaya Bello, based on his magnanimity, had to reduce the community financial commitment from 10% to 2.5% for the benefit of the communities. He disclosed that the fund for the projects is readily available with the release of a 30% initial tranche, to be followed by the second tranche which is contingent on the level of work done.He challenges the people to justify their confidence reposed in them by ensuring that the job is done according to specifications and time schedule. He urged them to take ownership of the projects by guarding against vandalisation and ensuring constant maintenance of the edifices. The GM said the Agency will spend over N14m on the construction of a borehole and a clinic at Abache Community, while Angwar – Ogebe will experience renovation of a classroom of their primary school and a borehole at the same cost. In their separate remarks, the Chairman of CPMC of Abache, Suleiman Mohammed and the Magajiya, Hajiya Fatima Mohammed commended Gov. Yahaya Bello and the management of CSDA for rescuing them from age-long water scarcity in the area. They assured of Delivery quality jobs within the stipulated time frame, stressing that the people will continue to mark this day as a day of liberty.